                                         JOHANNESBURG - Bafana Bafana midfielder Hlompho Kekana has withdrawn from the squad due to family reasons ahead of the clash with Senegal on Friday evening. Bafana have been rocked by a number of injuries and suspensions in the build-up to the crucial World Cup Qualifiers against Senegal at the Peter Mokaba Stadium, as well as a return leg in Dakar. Stuart Baxter is already sweating over the fitness of goalkeeper Itumeleng Khune and Captain Thulani Hlatshwayo due to facial and toe injuries respectively. Kekanaâ€™s Mamelodi Sundowns teammate Tiyani Mabunda has been called up to the national squad as the replacement.